    <edge source="Tradeoff process" target="Government">
      <data key="d7">4.0</data>
      <data key="d8">When it may be in the best interest of the Government to consider award to other than the lowest priced offeror or other than the highest technically rated offeror.&lt;SEP&gt;When using a tradeoff process, the Government may consider factors other than cost or price.&lt;SEP&gt;The perceived benefits of the higher priced proposal shall merit the additional cost.&lt;SEP&gt;Allows the Government to accept other than the lowest priced proposal.</data>
      <data key="d9">Acceptance,Appropriate,Benefits,Consideration</data>
      <data key="d10">doc-bbf1cc688706dd430bfe505423cb9745-chunk-000</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1782210818</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Tradeoff process" target="Evaluation factors">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The solicitation shall state whether all evaluation factors other than cost or price, when combined, are significantly more important than, approximately equal to, or significantly less important than cost or price.&lt;SEP&gt;All evaluation factors and significant subfactors that will affect contract award and their relative importance shall be clearly stated in the solicitation.</data>
      <data key="d9">Criteria,Importance</data>
      <data key="d10">doc-bbf1cc688706dd430bfe505423cb9745-chunk-000</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
