      <data key="d8">The contracting officer issues a new solicitation if an amendment is so substantial that it requires cancellation of the original solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;The contracting officer must issue an amendment if it is substantial and exceeds what offerors could have anticipated.&lt;SEP&gt;The contracting officer amends the solicitation when a proposal involves a departure from the stated requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;The contracting officer is responsible for issuing amendments to the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;The contracting officer documents the contract file with an amendment.&lt;SEP&gt;The contracting officer formalizes oral notices with an amendment.</data>
