    <edge source="Contracting officers" target="Facsimile">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Contracting officers should consider factors such as anticipated proposal size and volume, urgency of the requirement, availability and suitability of electronic commerce methods, and adequacy of administrative procedures and controls for receiving, identifying, recording, and safeguarding facsimile proposals, and ensuring their timely delivery to the designated proposal delivery location.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting officers may request offeror(s) to provide the complete, original signed proposal at a later date.</data>
